[6.67,"o","\r\n   _                 _\r\n  | | ___   __ _  __| | __ _ _ __ ___\r\n  | |/ _ \\ / _' |/ _' |/ _' | '_ ' _ \\\r\n  | | (_) | (_| | (_| | (_| | | | | | |\r\n  |_|\\___/ \\__,_|\\__,_|\\__,_|_| |_| |_|\r\n\r\n  spec → tests · contract · drift · MCP server\r\n\r\nUsage: loadam [options] [command]\r\n\r\nGenerate test rigs and MCP servers from any API spec. From spec to running rig\r\nin 60s.\r\n\r\nOptions:\r\n  -v, --version              print version\r\n  -h, --help                 display help for command\r\n\r\nCommands:\r\n  init [options] <spec>      Parse a spec and emit loadam.ir.json with inferred\r\n                             resource graph\r\n  auth                       Auth helpers\r\n  test [options] <spec>      Compile an OpenAPI spec into a runnable k6 test\r\n                             rig (smoke + load).\r\n  contract [options] <spec>  Compile an OpenAPI spec into a Schemathesis\r\n                             property-based contract suite.\r\n  diff [options] <spec>      Probe a live API and report drift against the spec\r\n                             (Markdown).\r\n  mcp [options] <spec>       Compile an OpenAPI spec into a runnable MCP server\r\n                             (stdio + HTTP).\r\n  completion <shell>         Print shell completion script (bash | zsh | fish)\r\n  update [options]           Check whether a newer version of @loadam/cli is on\r\n                             npm\r\n  help [command]             display help for command\r\n"]
